00:11:34.140 --> 00:11:35.740
Let me show you something
a little more subtle.

00:11:35.740 --> 00:11:37.970
This is natural differences
in rearing conditions,

00:11:37.970 --> 00:11:40.210
cultural transmission of rearing style

00:11:40.210 --> 00:11:41.130
and these are voles.

00:11:41.130 --> 00:11:42.586
Voles are biparental,

00:11:42.586 --> 00:11:44.280
both parents rear their young.

00:11:44.280 --> 00:11:45.630
And we can measure differences

00:11:45.630 --> 00:11:47.914
in total tactile contact with the young.

00:11:47.914 --> 00:11:50.490
We look at high contact
parents and low contact parents

00:11:50.490 --> 00:11:51.323
and important to remember,

00:11:51.323 --> 00:11:53.480
is that high contact offspring

00:11:53.480 --> 00:11:54.830
show differences in behavior,

00:11:54.830 --> 00:11:57.470
high contact offspring
become high contact parents

00:11:57.470 --> 00:11:59.420
and if you cross foster
them on the day of birth,

00:11:59.420 --> 00:12:00.910
you take low contact parents

00:12:00.910 --> 00:12:02.390
and put them with high contact parents,

00:12:02.390 --> 00:12:03.760
they become high contact parents.

00:12:03.760 --> 00:12:06.365
So this is a social
transmission of a rearing style.

00:12:06.365 --> 00:12:08.160
And if we look at the connections

00:12:08.160 --> 00:12:09.320
